<http://example.org/pt#stmt_10> prov:value "100 modified 2026-03-31T11:01:31.31Z",
        "Despite network name, network does not serve the northernmost stations on the Underground, though network does serve the southernmost station at Morden, the terminus of one of the two southern branches.",
        "During the early 1980s the London Transport Executive of the Greater London Council made a series of revisions to fares which introduced the fare zones.",
        "The first section became operational in 1863 when the Metropolitan Railway opened the world's first underground line between Paddington and Farringdon with wooden carriages and steam locomotives.",
        "The service is named after Queen Elizabeth II, who officially opened the line on 17 May 2022 during II Platinum Jubilee year; passenger services started on 24 May 2022.",
        "Tickets including zone 1 are usually more expensive than those involving only outer zones.",
        "cycle is tfl service false" .

