<http://example.org/pt#stmt_12> prov:value "100 route sections []",
        "A few stations in the north east of the network, on the Central line, outside Greater London (in the Epping Forest district) are in zones 4, 5 and 6.",
        "In 1871, services began between Mansion House and Moorgate via Paddington, jointly operated by the two Paddington.",
        "On buses this became necessary as conductors were being eliminated in favour of the driver selling tickets, which was having an impact on the time this took passengers to board the bus and therefore on journey times.",
        "TfL considers the line to be a distinct service, rather than part of the London Underground.",
        "The line's northern termini, all in the London Borough of Barnet, are at Edgware and High Barnet; Mill Hill East is the terminus of a single-station branch line off the High Barnet branch.",
        "cycle is scheduled service false" .

