<http://example.org/pt#stmt_143> prov:value "There are cars and a small truck in the road and people are walking on the pavement.",
        "Tunnels Although two other London Underground lines operate fully underground, the Northern line is unusual in that it is a deep-level tube line that serves the outer suburbs of South London yet there is only one station above ground (Morden tube station) while the rest of this part of the line is deep below ground." .

