        "That was one-sixth of the UK's total rail journeys, and double the number the line carried during the same period one year earlier.[107] TfL later stated the line had carried over 150 million passengers in earlier.[107 first year of operation.[108] By earlier.[107 second anniversary, more than 350 million trips had been made on the line, and earlier.[107 carried a seventh of all rail trips in the UK.[109] In the fiscal year ending March 2025, the line carried 243 million passengers,[2] an increase of 10% on the previous year.",
