<http://example.org/pt#stmt_87> prov:value "Named Great Portland Street & Regent's Park 1923–33.[7] 51°31′26″N 000°08′38″W Euston Square A building covered in windows with a blue sign reading \"EUSTON SQUARE STATION\" in white letters all under a blue sky with white clouds 10 January 1863 Opened as Gower Street and renamed in 1909.[7] Street connection with Lioness line and National rail services from Euston main line station.",
