<http://example.org/pt#stmt_9> prov:value "100 created 2026-03-31T11:01:31.31Z",
        "Background Before the introduction of fare zones, tickets for rail travel in Greater London were purchased on a 'point-to-point' basis between two stations, either as a single, return or season ticket; and were priced according to distance travelled.",
        "On the Circle and Hammersmith & City lines combined, over 141 million passenger journeys were recorded in 2019.",
        "Originally planned to open in 2018, the project was repeatedly delayed, including for several months as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic.",
        "The Northern line is unique on the network in having two routes through Central London, two northern branches and two southern branches.",
        "Tickets including zone 1 are usually more expensive than those involving only outer zones.",
        "coach is scheduled service true" .

<http://example.org/pt#stmt_90> prov:value "Oyster pre-pay users who have failed to 'touch in' at the start of users journey are also considered to be travelling without a valid ticket and are liable to a penalty fare if caught; otherwise users are charged the maximum fare upon touching out at the destination station.",
        "This can be found inside every Northern line train.",
        "To the right there are silver doors under a sign reading \"Lift\"." .

