<http://example.org/pt#stmt_93> prov:value "Change for National Rail services.map 11 Edgware branch Station Image Opened Additional information Edgware Disabled access 18 August 1924 Terminusmap 12 Burnt Oak 27 October 1924 Opened with Terminusmap current name, then renamed as \"Burnt Oak (Watling)\" approximately four years after Terminusmap opening; was reverted to Terminusmap original name in 1950.map 13 Colindale 18 August 1924 Used as a terminus for some trains travelling north.map 14 Hendon Central Disabled access 19 November 1923 map 15 Brent Cross Opened as \"Brent\"; renamed 20 July 1976.map 16 Golders Green Disabled access 22 June 1907 Originally a terminus; remains a terminus for some trains.map 17 Hampstead Originally proposed to be named \"Heath Street\"; this name can still be seen on wall tilings on station platform walls.map 18 Belsize Park One of eight London Underground stations that have deep-level air-raid shelters underneath stations.",
        "In an attempt to reduce the numbers of Travelcards being used by more than one person, an experiment took place at Brixton station in 2002.",
